Accept two integer values from the user and return their product. If the product is greater than 1000, then return their sum

Input Format

Line 1: 1st Number value Line 2: 2nd Number value

Constraints

1<=num1<=10^7 1<=num2,=10^7

Output Format

Line 1: Result of the operation

Sample Input 0

10
20
Sample Output 0

200
Sample Input 1

40
30
Sample Output 1

70
Sample Input 2

50
20
Sample Output 2

1000
Sample Input 3

100
200
Sample Output 3

300



#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int num1, num2;

    scanf("%d", &num1);
    scanf("%d", &num2);
    
    // Calculate product
    int product = num1 * num2;
    
    // Check if product is greater than 1000
    if (product > 1000) {
        // Return sum if product is greater than 1000
        printf("%d\n", num1 + num2);
    } else {
        // Return product if product is 1000 or less
        printf("%d\n", product);
    }
    
    return 0;
}
